This paper deals with the performance analysis of wireless sensor networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of Networked and Distributed Systems (cs.NI). The paper also involves stochastic processes and the analysis of unknown variables, which are topics that fall under Information Theory (cs.IT) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper uses numerical methods to solve fixed point equations, which is a topic that falls under Mathematical Analysis (cs.MA) and Probability (cs.PF).
